{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_71","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature | sed -n '1,210p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration\n     2\t  The `run start` command executes all stages of the standard flow preset\n     3\t  end-to-end using the workflow engine, persisting validated payloads,\n     4\t  rendered artifacts, journal events, and run snapshots at durable stage\n     5\t  boundaries.\n     6\t\n     7\t  # SC-START-001\n     8\t  Scenario: Happy path standard run completes all stages\n     9\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    10\t    And project \"alpha\" is selected as active\n    11\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    12\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    13\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    14\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    15\t    And the journal contains \"run_started\", \"stage_entered\", \"stage_completed\", and \"run_completed\" events\n    16\t    And payload and artifact records exist for all 8 standard stages\n    17\t\n    18\t  # SC-START-002\n    19\t  Scenario: Run start succeeds for quick_dev flow preset\n    20\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"beta\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    21\t    And project \"beta\" is selected as active\n    22\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    23\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    24\t    Then the command exits successfully\n    25\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    26\t    And the journal records \"plan_and_implement\", \"review\", \"apply_fixes\", and \"final_review\" in sequence\n    27\t    And payload and artifact records exist for all 4 quick_dev stages\n    28\t\n    29\t  # SC-START-003\n    30\t  Scenario: Run start rejects already-running project\n    31\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"gamma\" using flow \"standard\"\n    32\t    And project \"gamma\" is selected as active\n    33\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"running\" with an active run\n    34\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    35\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"not_started\"\n    36\t    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"running\")\n    37\t\n    38\t  # SC-START-004\n    39\t  Scenario: Run start rejects already-completed project\n    40\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    41\t    And project \"delta\" is selected as active\n    42\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    43\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    44\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"not_started\"\n    45\t    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"completed\")\n    46\t\n    47\t  # SC-START-005\n    48\t  Scenario: Run start validates workspace version before proceeding\n    49\t    Given a workspace with unsupported version\n    50\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    51\t    Then the command fails with error referencing workspace version\n    52\t    And no run state is mutated\n    53\t\n    54\t  # SC-START-006\n    55\t  Scenario: Run start requires an active project\n    56\t    Given an initialized workspace with no active project\n    57\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    58\t    Then the command fails with error referencing active project\n    59\t    And no run state is mutated\n    60\t\n    61\t  # SC-START-007\n    62\t  Scenario: Stage plan derives from flow definition with prompt_review enabled\n    63\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"echo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    64\t    And prompt_review.enabled is true (default)\n    65\t    When the stage plan is derived\n    66\t    Then the plan includes all 8 standard stages in canonical order\n    67\t    And the first stage is \"prompt_review\"\n    68\t\n    69\t  # SC-START-008\n    70\t  Scenario: Stage plan skips prompt_review when disabled\n    71\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"foxtrot\" using flow \"standard\"\n    72\t    And prompt_review.enabled is false\n    73\t    When the stage plan is derived\n    74\t    Then the plan includes 7 stages (all except prompt_review)\n    75\t    And the first stage is \"planning\"\n    76\t\n    77\t  # SC-START-009\n    78\t  Scenario: Preflight checks validate all stages before any mutation\n    79\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"golf\" using flow \"standard\"\n    80\t    And the backend is unavailable\n    81\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    82\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"preflight\"\n    83\t    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"not_started\")\n    84\t    And the journal has no new events beyond project_created\n    85\t\n    86\t  # SC-START-010\n    87\t  Scenario: Stage-to-role mapping is deterministic\n    88\t    Given the standard flow stage sequence\n    89\t    Then each stage maps to exactly one backend role\n    90\t    And the mapping is consistent across invocations\n    91\t\n    92\t  # SC-START-011\n    93\t  Scenario: Atomic stage commit persists payload, artifact, journal event, and snapshot\n    94\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"hotel\" using flow \"standard\"\n    95\t    And the run has started and is executing stages\n    96\t    When a stage completes successfully\n    97\t    Then a payload record is written to history/payloads\n    98\t    And a matching artifact record is written to history/artifacts\n    99\t    And a stage_completed event is appended to the journal\n   100\t    And the run snapshot is updated with the next stage cursor\n   101\t\n   102\t  # SC-START-012\n   103\t  Scenario: Run failure records failure in journal and snapshot\n   104\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"india\" using flow \"standard\"\n   105\t    And a stage invocation fails during execution\n   106\t    When the engine handles the failure\n   107\t    Then a run_failed event is appended to the journal\n   108\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n   109\t    And the status_summary includes the failed stage name\n   110\t\n   111\t  # SC-START-013\n   112\t  Scenario: Runtime logs are best-effort and do not affect durable state\n   113\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"juliet\" using flow \"standard\"\n   114\t    And runtime log writes are failing\n   115\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   116\t    Then the command completes successfully despite log failures\n   117\t    And all durable state (journal, payloads, artifacts, snapshot) is correct\n   118\t\n   119\t  # SC-START-014\n   120\t  Scenario: Journal sequence numbers are monotonically increasing\n   121\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"kilo\" using flow \"standard\"\n   122\t    When the user runs \"run start\" and it completes\n   123\t    Then all journal events have strictly increasing sequence numbers\n   124\t    And no sequence gaps exist\n   125\t\n   126\t  # SC-START-015\n   127\t  Scenario: Run ID is unique per run invocation\n   128\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"lima\" using flow \"standard\"\n   129\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   130\t    Then the run_started event contains a run_id matching \"run-YYYYMMDDHHMMSS\" format\n   131\t    And the run_id is consistent across all events for this run\n   132\t\n   133\t  # SC-START-016\n   134\t  Scenario: Post-run queries work correctly after successful run\n   135\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"mike\" using flow \"standard\"\n   136\t    And the user has completed \"run start\" successfully\n   137\t    When the user runs \"run status\"\n   138\t    Then the output shows \"completed\"\n   139\t    When the user runs \"run history\"\n   140\t    Then the output includes all stage events and payload/artifact records\n   141\t\n   142\t  # SC-START-017\n   143\t  Scenario: Run start supports all four built-in flow presets\n   144\t    Given an initialized workspace with projects using flows \"standard\", \"quick_dev\", \"docs_change\", \"ci_improvement\"\n   145\t    When the user runs \"run start\" for each project\n   146\t    Then all four flow presets complete successfully\n   147\t\n   148\t  # SC-START-018\n   149\t  Scenario: Prompt-review-disabled run start completes with 7 stages\n   150\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"november\" using flow \"standard\"\n   151\t    And prompt_review.enabled is false\n   152\t    And project \"november\" is selected as active\n   153\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n   154\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   155\t    Then the command exits successfully\n   156\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n   157\t    And payload and artifact records exist for 7 stages (all except prompt_review)\n   158\t    And the journal contains no \"stage_entered\" or \"stage_completed\" events for \"prompt_review\"\n   159\t    And the first stage_entered event is for \"planning\"\n   160\t\n   161\t  # SC-START-019\n   162\t  Scenario: Preflight failure leaves all canonical state unchanged\n   163\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"oscar\" using flow \"standard\"\n   164\t    And project \"oscar\" is selected as active\n   165\t    And the backend is unavailable for preflight\n   166\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   167\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"preflight\"\n   168\t    And the run snapshot is byte-identical to its pre-run state\n   169\t    And the journal is byte-identical to its pre-run state\n   170\t    And no payload or artifact files exist\n   171\t    And no sessions were created or modified\n   172\t\n   173\t  # SC-START-020\n   174\t  Scenario: Mid-stage failure exposes no partial durable history\n   175\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"papa\" using flow \"standard\"\n   176\t    And project \"papa\" is selected as active\n   177\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n   178\t    And persistence will fail during the first stage commit\n   179\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n   180\t    Then the command fails\n   181\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n   182\t    And no payload or artifact files exist for any stage\n   183\t    And no \"stage_completed\" event exists in the journal\n   184\t    And the journal ends with a \"run_failed\" event referencing the failed stage\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
