{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_72","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_completion_rounds.feature | sed -n '1,120p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Completion Rounds, Late-Stage Acceptance, and Durable Amendments\n     2\t  When a late stage (completion_panel, acceptance_qa, final_review) returns\n     3\t  a non-approved outcome, the engine queues durable amendments and advances\n     4\t  the completion round, restarting from planning. The completion guard\n     5\t  blocks run_completed when pending amendments remain.\n     6\t\n     7\t  # SC-CR-001\n     8\t  Scenario: Late-stage conditionally_approved triggers completion round advancement\n     9\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    10\t    And project \"cr-alpha\" is selected as active\n    11\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    12\t    When the user starts a run where completion_panel returns \"conditionally_approved\" with amendments\n    13\t    Then the engine queues durable amendment files under projects/cr-alpha/amendments/\n    14\t    And the journal contains an \"amendment_queued\" event with the amendment body\n    15\t    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with from_round=1 to_round=2\n    16\t    And the engine restarts from planning (stage_entered for planning appears a second time)\n    17\t    And the planning invocation context includes pending_amendments\n    18\t    And after successful planning commit the amendment files are removed from disk\n    19\t    And the run snapshot shows completion_rounds=2 after completion\n    20\t    And the run snapshot amendment_queue is empty\n    21\t\n    22\t  # SC-CR-002\n    23\t  Scenario: Late-stage request_changes triggers completion round advancement\n    24\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-beta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    25\t    And project \"cr-beta\" is selected as active\n    26\t    When the user starts a run where acceptance_qa returns \"request_changes\" with amendments\n    27\t    Then the engine follows the same completion-round path as conditionally_approved\n    28\t    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with source_stage=\"acceptance_qa\"\n    29\t\n    30\t  # SC-CR-003\n    31\t  Scenario: Late-stage rejected causes terminal failure\n    32\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-gamma\" using flow \"standard\"\n    33\t    And project \"cr-gamma\" is selected as active\n    34\t    When the user starts a run where completion_panel returns \"rejected\"\n    35\t    Then the run fails with failure_class \"qa_review_outcome_failure\"\n    36\t    And no \"completion_round_advanced\" event exists in the journal\n    37\t    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\"\n    38\t\n    39\t  # SC-CR-004\n    40\t  Scenario: Late-stage approved advances to the next late stage\n    41\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    42\t    And project \"cr-delta\" is selected as active\n    43\t    When the user starts a run where all late stages return \"approved\"\n    44\t    Then the run completes normally with completion_rounds=1\n    45\t    And completion_panel transitions to acceptance_qa transitions to final_review\n    46\t\n    47\t  # SC-CR-005\n    48\t  Scenario: Non-late-stage conditionally_approved does not queue amendments\n    49\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-epsilon\" using flow \"standard\"\n    50\t    And project \"cr-epsilon\" is selected as active\n    51\t    When the user starts a run where review returns \"conditionally_approved\"\n    52\t    Then the run completes normally\n    53\t    And the amendment_queue in run.json is empty\n    54\t    And no \"amendment_queued\" or \"completion_round_advanced\" events exist\n    55\t\n    56\t  # SC-CR-006\n    57\t  Scenario: Multiple completion rounds accumulate correctly\n    58\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-zeta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    59\t    And project \"cr-zeta\" is selected as active\n    60\t    When the user starts a run where completion_panel triggers round 2 and acceptance_qa triggers round 3\n    61\t    Then the journal contains two \"completion_round_advanced\" events\n    62\t    And the final run snapshot shows completion_rounds=3\n    63\t    And the run completes normally\n    64\t\n    65\t  # SC-CR-007\n    66\t  Scenario: Completion guard blocks run_completed when disk amendments exist\n    67\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-eta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    68\t    And project \"cr-eta\" is selected as active\n    69\t    And a durable amendment file exists under projects/cr-eta/amendments/\n    70\t    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    71\t    Then the run fails with error containing \"completion blocked\" or \"pending amendments\"\n    72\t    And the amendment file remains on disk\n    73\t\n    74\t  # SC-CR-008\n    75\t  Scenario: Completion guard checks both snapshot queue and disk\n    76\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-theta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    77\t    And the run snapshot has non-empty amendment_queue.pending\n    78\t    When the engine reaches the completion boundary\n    79\t    Then the completion guard fires and blocks run_completed\n    80\t    And the run fails with \"completion blocked\"\n    81\t\n    82\t  # SC-CR-009\n    83\t  Scenario: Resume with pending late-stage amendments\n    84\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-iota\" using flow \"standard\"\n    85\t    And a previous run failed after completion_round_advanced but before planning in round 2\n    86\t    And durable amendment files exist on disk\n    87\t    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n    88\t    Then the engine reconciles amendments from disk into the run snapshot\n    89\t    And the engine restarts from planning with amendments in context\n    90\t    And the amendments are drained after planning commit\n    91\t    And the run completes normally\n    92\t\n    93\t  # SC-CR-010\n    94\t  Scenario: Cycle advancement emitted when entering implementation from completion round\n    95\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-kappa\" using flow \"standard\"\n    96\t    When a completion round restarts from planning and advances to implementation\n    97\t    Then a \"cycle_advanced\" event is emitted for the new work cycle\n    98\t    And the implementation invocation runs in the new cycle\n    99\t\n   100\t  # SC-CR-011\n   101\t  Scenario: Amendment queue drain is idempotent\n   102\t    Given amendments are queued in both snapshot and disk\n   103\t    When planning commit triggers the drain\n   104\t    Then all amendments are removed from disk\n   105\t    And the snapshot amendment_queue.pending is empty\n   106\t    And amendment_queue.processed_count is incremented\n   107\t\n   108\t  # SC-CR-012\n   109\t  Scenario: Amendment persistence is atomic with batch rollback\n   110\t    Given a late stage returns conditionally_approved with follow_ups\n   111\t    When the engine persists amendment files\n   112\t    Then each amendment file is written atomically (temp + rename)\n   113\t    And if any amendment write fails, already-written files from the same batch are rolled back\n   114\t    And the run fails without partial amendments visible\n   115\t    And the failure invariant holds: no queue entry becomes visible without a matching file\n   116\t\n   117\t  # SC-CR-013\n   118\t  Scenario: Completion guard leaves snapshot in resumable state\n   119\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-lambda\" using flow \"standard\"\n   120\t    And a durable amendment file exists under projects/cr-lambda/amendments/\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
