{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_80","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Conformance executors need to implement the Gherkin scenarios, not placeholder checks**: the registry currently satisfies ID/count bookkeeping, but many executors do not drive the behavior described by the feature corpus.\n   - Current: [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L880) implements `SC-START-001` by creating a fixture and calling `run status`; [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L1060) implements `SC-START-018` by calling `flow show standard` and even asserting `Stage count: 8`; [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L1605) reduces `SC-CR-001` to `run status`; [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L1970) reduces `RD-001` to `project show`. Those do not match the source scenarios in [run_start_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature#L7), [run_start_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature#L148), [run_completion_rounds.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_completion_rounds.feature#L7), and [requirements_drafting.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature#L8).\n   - Expected: each executor should drive the actual CLI/domain path under test and assert the durable outcomes the feature file names: `run start`/`run resume`/`requirements draft`, completed or failed snapshots, journal events, payload/artifact persistence, amendment queue behavior, and other scenario-specific invariants. `SC-START-018` specifically must verify a 7-stage run with no `prompt_review` events, not a static `flow show` result of 8 stages.\n   - Reference: [prompt.md](/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/prompt.md#L249), [20260313003501-spec.md](/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/014-conformance-runner-and-ci-gate/20260313003501-spec.md#L35), [20260313003501-spec.md](/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/014-conformance-runner-and-ci-gate/20260313003501-spec.md#L40)\n\n2. **Fail-fast output currently reports the failing scenario twice**: this misses the explicit “report once” requirement.\n   - Current: [runner.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/runner.rs#L122) prints the failure line and reason immediately, then [conformance.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/conformance.rs#L95) returns `ConformanceScenarioFailed`, which [main.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/main.rs#L14) prints again on exit.\n   - Expected: preserve fail-fast and non-zero exit, but emit the failing scenario ID and reason once. Either the runner should only record failure state and the CLI should print the final failure, or the CLI should avoid re-printing an already-emitted failure.\n   - Reference: [20260313003501-spec.md](/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/014-conformance-runner-and-ci-gate/20260313003501-spec.md#L37)\n\n3. **The required CLI/unit coverage is not actually present**: the new tests do not exercise several acceptance-criteria paths they claim to cover.\n   - Current: [tests/cli.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L3934) labels a duplicate-ID test but only re-runs successful `conformance list`; [tests/cli.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L3950) labels a fail-fast test but runs a passing single-scenario filter; [conformance_spec_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/conformance_spec_test.rs#L275) checks panic accounting only and does not verify temp-workspace cleanup.\n   - Expected: add real integration coverage for duplicate-ID failure and fail-fast stopping behavior, plus unit coverage that proves temp workspace cleanup after scenario failure/panic.\n   - Reference: [20260313003501-spec.md](/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/014-conformance-runner-and-ci-gate/20260313003501-spec.md#L43), [20260313003501-spec.md](/root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/014-conformance-runner-and-ci-gate/20260313003501-spec.md#L44)\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Split [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs) by feature or scenario family. The current 2.3k-line monolith makes spec drift hard to audit and directly contributed to mismatches like `SC-START-018`."}}
