{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_58","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature | sed -n '1,120p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Stage Contracts\n     2\t  Stage contracts define schema validation, semantic validation, and\n     3\t  deterministic Markdown rendering for every stage in every built-in\n     4\t  flow preset. Contract evaluation follows a fixed order: schema first,\n     5\t  semantics second, rendering last. Failures at any step short-circuit\n     6\t  subsequent steps.\n     7\t\n     8\t  @SC-EVAL-001\n     9\t  Scenario: Successful planning contract evaluation\n    10\t    Given a planning stage contract\n    11\t    When a valid planning payload is submitted\n    12\t    Then schema validation passes\n    13\t    And semantic validation passes\n    14\t    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    15\t    And the result carries no outcome failure\n    16\t\n    17\t  @SC-EVAL-002\n    18\t  Scenario: Successful execution contract evaluation\n    19\t    Given an execution stage contract\n    20\t    When a valid execution payload is submitted\n    21\t    Then schema validation passes\n    22\t    And semantic validation passes\n    23\t    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    24\t    And the result carries no outcome failure\n    25\t\n    26\t  @SC-EVAL-003\n    27\t  Scenario: Successful validation contract evaluation with passing outcome\n    28\t    Given a validation stage contract\n    29\t    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"approved\" is submitted\n    30\t    Then schema validation passes\n    31\t    And semantic validation passes\n    32\t    And a deterministic Markdown artifact is produced\n    33\t    And the result carries no outcome failure\n    34\t\n    35\t  @SC-EVAL-004\n    36\t  Scenario: Schema validation failure prevents semantic validation\n    37\t    Given a planning stage contract\n    38\t    When an invalid JSON payload missing required fields is submitted\n    39\t    Then schema validation fails with failure class \"schema_validation_failure\"\n    40\t    And semantic validation does not run\n    41\t    And rendering does not run\n    42\t    And no success bundle is returned\n    43\t\n    44\t  @SC-EVAL-005\n    45\t  Scenario: Domain validation failure prevents rendering\n    46\t    Given an execution stage contract\n    47\t    When a schema-valid payload with empty change_summary and no steps is submitted\n    48\t    Then schema validation passes\n    49\t    And semantic validation fails with failure class \"domain_validation_failure\"\n    50\t    And rendering does not run\n    51\t    And no success bundle is returned\n    52\t\n    53\t  @SC-EVAL-006\n    54\t  Scenario: QA/review outcome failure returns error with no success bundle\n    55\t    Given a validation stage contract\n    56\t    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"rejected\" is submitted\n    57\t    Then schema validation passes\n    58\t    And semantic validation passes\n    59\t    And the result is an error with failure class \"qa_review_outcome_failure\"\n    60\t    And no success bundle is returned\n    61\t    And rendering does not run\n    62\t\n    63\t  @SC-EVAL-007\n    64\t  Scenario: Every stage in every built-in flow has contract coverage\n    65\t    Given the set of all built-in flow presets\n    66\t    Then every stage in every preset resolves to exactly one contract\n    67\t    And no stage is left without a contract\n    68\t\n    69\t  @SC-EVAL-008\n    70\t  Scenario: Deterministic rendering produces identical output\n    71\t    Given a validated planning payload\n    72\t    When the payload is rendered twice\n    73\t    Then both renders are byte-identical\n    74\t\n    75\t  @SC-EVAL-009\n    76\t  Scenario: Non-passing review outcomes are not treated as schema or domain failures\n    77\t    Given a validation stage contract\n    78\t    When a valid validation payload with outcome \"request_changes\" is submitted\n    79\t    Then schema validation passes\n    80\t    And semantic validation passes\n    81\t    And the result is an error with failure class \"qa_review_outcome_failure\"\n    82\t    And the failure class is not \"schema_validation_failure\"\n    83\t    And the failure class is not \"domain_validation_failure\"\n    84\t    And no success bundle is returned\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
