{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_64","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Registry fidelity**: large parts of the conformance registry are still placeholder executors, so `conformance run` is not actually executing the checked-in public contract.\nCurrent: [scenarios.rs#L861](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L861) through [scenarios.rs#L949](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L949) implement the entire `SC-EVAL-*` family with `flow show` / `project show` checks instead of stage-contract evaluation; [scenarios.rs#L1999](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L1999) through [scenarios.rs#L2060](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L2060) reduce `SC-CR-005` through `SC-CR-012` to `run status`; [scenarios.rs#L2371](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L2371) and [scenarios.rs#L2469](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L2469) reduce most `RD-*` scenarios to `run status`; and [scenarios.rs#L2330](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L2330) lets `RD-001` pass with either `completed` or `awaiting_answers`, even though the feature requires generated questions plus `awaiting_answers`.\nExpected: Replace the remaining stubs with executors that drive the actual CLI/domain path and assert the durable outcomes named in the feature corpus.\nReference: [stage_contracts.feature#L8](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/stage_contracts.feature#L8), [run_completion_rounds.feature#L47](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_completion_rounds.feature#L47), [requirements_drafting.feature#L8](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature#L8)\n\n2. **CLI acceptance coverage**: the required integration coverage for duplicate-ID failure and fail-fast stopping behavior is still missing.\nCurrent: [tests/cli.rs#L3934](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L3934) only reruns successful `conformance list`; [tests/cli.rs#L3957](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L3957) runs a passing single-scenario filter, not a fail-fast case; [tests/cli.rs#L3985](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L3985) does not assert a non-zero exit or that remaining selected scenarios were marked not run.\nExpected: Add real CLI/integration tests that exercise duplicate-ID failure at the command surface and a selected multi-scenario run where the first failure stops execution and leaves later selected scenarios not run.\nReference: Loop 14 acceptance criteria requiring CLI coverage for duplicate-ID detection and fail-fast stopping behavior\n\n3. **Cutover guard scope**: the regression guard does not scan all production `src/` code.\nCurrent: [cutover_guard.rs#L39](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/cutover_guard.rs#L39) skips the entire `conformance_spec` subtree, so any legacy `.ralph/` or `multibackend-orchestration` reference added under `src/contexts/conformance_spec/**` would be invisible to the guard.\nExpected: Scan the full `src/` tree and exempt only the minimal self-referential lines/comments needed for the guard implementation itself.\nReference: Loop 14 acceptance criterion requiring the cutover guard to fail on legacy workspace/runtime references under production `src/`\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Split [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs) by feature family. The current monolith is already large enough that spec drift is hard to spot and audit."}}
